% Instructions
- Follow MCP tool definition pattern
- Count passed/failed steps from stepResults array
- Calculate duration from startedAt/completedAt difference
- Return summary, not full step details (use get_test_run for details)
- Log execution start/end to stderr
- Handle timeout scenarios gracefully

% Deliverable
A TypeScript module at src/tools/run-test-plan.ts exporting the runTestPlanTool function.

% Implementation Assumptions
- Test plan exists before execution
- Execution may take significant time (async operation)
- MCP response is sent after execution completes
- Duration is in milliseconds
